# SmartHaus M365 AI Workforce AI Agent Rules (Launcher)

## Status

Review document to check yourself

## Quick start

```bash
make ai-status || true
make ai-health-check || true
make ai-perf-check || true
```

## Validate (one command)

```bash
make ai-validate
```

Runs quality gate (lint + tests + docs) plus contract and traceability gates.

## Quality gates

```bash
make quality-gate
make test-all
make lint-all
make contract-gate
make traceability-gate
```

## North Star alignment (must)

- Hyper-local neighbor-to-neighbor help marketplace
- App-first development (iOS native, web secondary)
- Simple, safe task scope (no permits, no licensed work)
- Self-service platform (SMARTHAUS maintenance-only)
- Direct payments between neighbors (no platform processing in v1)
- v1 scope lock: location + category filtering only (no advanced matching)

## Required reading

- Operations/NORTHSTAR.md
- Operations/EXECUTION_PLAN.md
- contracts/localhelp_v1_contract.yml
- contracts/traceability_manifest.yml

## Mandatory validation rules

- NEVER assume previous work is done; ALWAYS validate
- ALWAYS run tests; failing tests = not done
- VERIFY dependencies and functionality; docs ≠ working code
- If you can't run it, it doesn't work

## Forbidden actions (short)

- Skipping validation or trusting claims
- Implementing v2+ features in v1 (advanced matching, payments, ratings)
- "Good enough" code, skipped tests, known bugs, partial features
- Vague commits without rationale/decisions
- Underusing AI on complex end-to-end work
